### Handheld RF Analyzer
#### Solicitation Number: 2023-14693
#### Tender Closing Date: Thursday, February 24, 2023 at 13:00 Eastern Standard Time

The Department of National Defence, National Capital Region, invites vendors to submit their proposals for the supply of two (2) handheld RF analyzers. The analyzers will be used in laboratory and field environments by the Communications Electronic Warfare (CEW) group of Defence Research & Development Canada – Ottawa Research Centre (DRDC ORC) for the measurement of RF signals in various configurations.

#### Key Requirements

*   Supply of two (2) handheld RF analyzers, as required by the CEW group of DRDC ORC;
*   Analyzers must be capable of performing measurement of RF signals in various configurations in laboratory and field environments;
*   Analyzers must meet the technical specifications outlined in the solicitation documents.

#### Purchase Information

*   Part Number: [Insert Part Number];
*   NASA GSIN: N5975 (Electrical Hardware and Supplies);
*   Procurement Category: Goods and Services (GD);
*   Trade Agreements: Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA).

#### Tendering Process

The solicitation is open to all qualified vendors. Proposals can be submitted electronically or by mail. Vendors must ensure their proposals conform to the requirements outlined in the solicitation documents.

#### Submission Requirements

*   Proposals must be submitted in English or French;
*   Proposals must contain the required documentation, including:
    *   Company profile;
    *   Proof of employment;
    *   Technical specifications and certifications;
    *   Pricing information;
    *   Other relevant supporting documents.

#### Contact Information

For more information, please contact Susanne Hall at (613) 993-7069 or via email at [susanne.hall@forces.gc.ca](mailto:susanne.hall@forces.gc.ca). Additional documents, including the RFP and solicitation documents, can be found on the [Canada Buys website](https://canadabuys.canada.ca).

#### Languages of Bid

The solicitation and materials will be provided in English and French. Proposals must be submitted in English or French.

#### Preference to Canadian Goods and Services

The Government of Canada has implemented a policy of preference to Canadian goods and services. Vendors must be aware of this policy and ensure their proposal complies with it.

#### Compliance and Restrictions

Vendors must comply with all applicable laws and regulations,
